race.comment: LITTLE BIGHORN (3) resumed further improved narrowly beaten as favourite at Werribee. Maps for a soft run and will be fitter again. Rawiller sticks aboard and he can go one better. SILVALOA (6) made an impression winning at Swan Hill on debut. He resumed in much stronger at Caulfield Heath and was short of a run. Gets in well with the 3kg claim and will settle back and likely finish hard. MR MARKLE (7) came from back in the field to place at Tatura first-up. Raced a $3 favourite and he showed plenty early doors. Has a wide gate but looks to be back on track. ZENACITY (13) has the outside gate, but her best form stacks right up. We are likely to see more from her third-up.
